<subSubSection id="E550B9889FA83107EA82897EB5EA0E37" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" type="note">
<paragraph id="5EF2E84396A921490BB0EA7B530D0AA6" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AED8F9CA3C3D99FCA315BD2F0B94829E" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">
Open growth form; leaves linear or ensiform; inflorescences bearing many flowers; staminate flowers with short or long filaments (0.9-2.8 mm); pistillate flowers with long outer tepals (2.3-5.3 
<normalizedToken id="AD90D6F99B6F6255D00B7C36C9BFF19A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.2-2.6 mm); ovary trilocular, intermediate length (1.8-4.6 mm); fruit globose, few seeds per fruit (4-12); seeds long and narrow (1.8-3.6 
<normalizedToken id="9A0A490E62307620447567FB14DDE7FB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.7-1.6 mm). Type: 
<taxonomicName id="31A7902B282E711F58E217E775EFB250" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia argyrocoma" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="argyrocoma">
<emphasis id="0D2208B6E61FFC890C049868332E05F4" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Astelia argyrocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
A.Heller &amp; Skottsb., designated here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
